          "body": "Verses 3:10-15 are the most structurally regular section of the chapter: nineteen iterations of 'his son' from Rehoboam through Josiah. The regularity is itself the point. Through righteous kings (Asa, Jehoshaphat, Hezekiah) and wicked ones (Joram, Ahaz, Manasseh), through covenant renewals and covenant betrayals, through temple reformations and temple profanations, the biological line held. God did not cancel the Davidic covenant when Manasseh filled Jerusalem with blood (2 Kings 21:16). He did not terminate it when Ahaz closed the temple and sacrificed his son in the fire (2 Kings 16:3). He sustained the biological thread through every generation that deserved to see it cut. The Chronicler does not stop to note which kings were faithful — he is not writing a character evaluation here. He is writing a covenant-persistence record."
