    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text *means* — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the author's intent in his original context. 1 Chronicles 3 is a covenant-historical document embedded in a genealogical prologue written for a post-exilic community that desperately needed to know whether God's promise to David still stood. The movements below trace the chapter's argument in four pericopes. Hebrew lexical notes supplement, never lead.",
